summary:
The Security Council,
Reaffirming its resolution 1359 (2001) and previous resolutions on Western Sahara,
Noting the Secretary-General's letter of 12 November 2001 (S/2001/1067),

1. Decides to extend the mandate of MINURSO until 28 February 2002;
2. Requests the Secretary-General to provide an interim report by 15 January 2002 and an assessment of the situation by 18 February 2002;
3. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
